## Exercise 2

What is gitignore?
.gitignore is a special file that tells Git:

"Hey Git! Please ignore these files/folders. I donâ€™t want them in my repository."

âœ… Why do we use .gitignore?
To avoid committing:

Temporary files (*.log, *.class)

Personal config files (.env)

Output folders like log/, build/

ðŸ› ï¸ How to Use .gitignore (Hands-On Lab Steps)
